# Scale fill example

`scale_fill_brewer` works just the same as `scale_colour_brewer` but for fill colours.



<pre class="mcode">
p <- ggplot(diamonds, aes(x = price, fill = cut)) +
  geom_histogram(position = "dodge", binwidth = 1000)
p <-  p + scale_fill_brewer()

plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>
